==Notable people==

*Deng Chao (born 1979), actor
*François Cheng (born 1929), French academician
*Zhang Dinghuang (1895–1986), academic
*Grace Glenn (born 1998), American artistic gymnast
*Hu Hsen-Hsu (1894 – 1968), founder of plant taxonomy and pioneer of modern botany and paleobotany in China
*Cheng Maoyun (1900 – 1957), composer of the National Anthem of the Republic of China
*Duan Yongping (born 1961), Chinese-American entrepreneur
*Zhi Yueying (born 1961), educator

==Sport==
Nanchang is the site of Jiangxi International Women&#x27;s Tennis Open.

