<doc id="386936" wikidata="Q778313" url="?curid=386936" title="Piastów">
<text>Piastów is a town in central Poland, near Warsaw, with 23,331 inhabitants (2006 est). It is situated in the Masovian Voivodship (since 1999); previously, it was in Warszawa Voivodship (1975–1998). With 3963 persons/km², it is the second most densely populated township in Poland (after Świętochłowice).

In the Middle Age, the villages of Żdżary and Utrata existed in the place of today&#x27;s&#x27; Piastów. Piastów is served by Piastów railway station.</text><links>
